{
  "stem": "14060.6",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "You were not cooped up in there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And so my father, my brother and I went.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "The next older brother of my father [?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "Uli ?] is Gyula, who was the father of Gershon, the professor, my cousin, who survived in the Munka Tabor.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "Was in the First World War as a soldier.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And I remember we used to make-- poke fun at him that he used to tell always his military stories.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "Nevertheless, for some reason or other, he was the only one-- and we didn't take him sometimes seriously with all his war stories-- he exactly said about Auschwitz and what's happening there.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And nobody believed him, including my parents-- nobody.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "They considered him half crazy.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "So much so that on the 29th of June, when the ghetto was cleared and taken out to near the railway station into a half-built factory, he left his wife and daughter, and he escaped into the forest.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "He somehow or other maintained himself for two, three months.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "Eventually one of the Hungarian forest guides gave him-- reported him.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "He was taken to some sort of a internment camp.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And from there, even at the later stage in August when he was sent to Auschwitz, and he never came back.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "You know, the, the, the, the-- I don't call it religiousness, but the, the, the enthusiasm with which the Hungarians pursued the German final solution is equal to none.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "They did a perfect job.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And if you really realize what administration it must've taken to take 650,000 people out from villages of towns and organize railways and, and, and register them, and take their properties away, and everything in a matter of three months-- this is a feat not equaled in many history of organization.",
      "word_count": 51
    }
  ],
